FBIS4-24540 "drchi104_v_94001" FBIS-CHI-94-104 Daily Report 27 May 1994 TAIWAN Reportage on Visit of Former Soviet Prime Minister Reportage on Visit of Former Soviet Prime Minister Ryzkov Arrives in Taipei OW2705134694 Taipei CNA in English 1258 GMT 27 May 94 OW2705134694 Taipei CNA English BFN [By Flor Wang] [Text] Taipei, May 27 (CNA) -- Nikolai I. Ryzkov, former prime minister of the now defunct Soviet Union, arrived in Taipei Friday [27 May] for a week-long visit. Ryzkov, accompanied by his wife and a six-member party, is here at the invitation of the Republic of China [ROC] & Russia International Association for Humanitarian Dialogue. Cheng Po-chiu, West Asian affairs director of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, officially greeted the Ryzkov delegation at Chiang Kai-shek International Airport. Ryzkov, 65, who was first elected as secretary-general of the Soviet Communist Party by Mikhail Gorbachev in 1985 before being elevated to the post of prime minister, resigned in 1990 after objecting to the 500-day economic reform program launched by the Soviet Government. During his stay here, Ryzkov will call on President Li Teng-hui, Premier Lien Chan, and Foreign Affairs Minister Chien Fu. He will also deliver a speech at the Legislative Yuan and hold seminars with local business leaders.
